<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 22 at 8:17AM EST  by NWS Albany</headline>
<description>...Icy Spots Through Late Morning From Freezing Fog and Freezing
Rain...
Temperatures remaining in the low to mid 20s in the Mohawk Valley
and parts of Saratoga County combined with fog have resulted in
slippery travel conditions this morning.
Further east, showers are slowly exiting but with temperatures
still in the low to mid 30s, some icy spots may still be in place
through late morning.
Use caution if driving or walking on untreated walkways.</description>
